    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "In general, this is because we allow widget errors to be completely unhandled, which results in logging. Probably an explicit call to ip.showtraceback() should be made somewhere. It seems like logging is the right thing to do in comms in general (by default), but not the right thing to do in widget callbacks, since they represent user action. But I'm not actually sure about that.\n"
